  "response": "Opinions on overrated travel destinations can vary, but some commonly mentioned places include:\n\n1. Times Square, New York City\n2. Venice, Italy (due to overcrowding)\n3. Paris, France (specifically tourist areas)\n4. Cancun, Mexico\n5. Dubai, UAE\n6. Pisa, Italy (mainly for the Leaning Tower)\n7. Hollywood Walk of Fame\n8. Stonehenge, UK\n9. Machu Picchu (during peak tourist season)\n10. Bali, Indonesia (in very touristy areas)\n\nThe perception of being \"overrated\" often relates to:\n- Excessive crowds\n- High prices\n- Overhyped expectations\n- Lack of authenticity\n- Commercialization\n\nKeep in mind that travel experiences are subjective, and what one person finds overrated, another might thoroughly enjoy.",
